name: Observe -> wiring between consecutive modules (all inter-module cable pairs),
description: Systematically inspect and trace each pair of cables between every pair of adjacent modules (power→CM1, CM1→CM2, …, CM8→load) to determine whether the outgoing 12V and 0V lines from one module are correctly mated to the corresponding 12V and 0V inputs of the next module, and identify any crossed, swapped, or open interconnections. Do not alter internal module circuitry; only verify how the fast‑connection terminals are plugged together., outcome='All inspected inter-module connections from PSU → Control Cubes 1–8 → Load are consistently wired with (+) to (+) and (−) to (−); no POLARITY INVERSION detected.  \nOne open connection was found: Control Input Cable (+) 6 has its port_n disconnected (floating).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=460.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 6 inter-module cabling and internal series path,
description: With the battery installed and all switches ON, measure continuity (or DC voltage drop) along the main 12V series line through Control Module 6: from its incoming + terminal to its outgoing + terminal, and from incoming − to outgoing −, while gently wiggling the connectors. This is to verify whether the previously observed open on Control Input Cable (+) 6 is indeed breaking the series path through CM6 or if there is an additional internal open in that module., outcome='All requested continuity and voltage measurements on Control Module 6 (incoming and outgoing + and − lines) could not be performed because the multimeter is unavailable. No diagnostic data about the 12V series path through CM6 was obtained.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=160.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control Input Cable (+) 6 connection,
description: Physically plug/re-seat the previously found open Control Input Cable (+) 6 fast-connection terminal into its mating port on Control Module 6 so that the + line from Control Module 5 properly enters Control Module 6. Do not alter any other wiring or internal circuitry., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control Input Cable (+) 6 connection,
description: Inspect the fast-connection terminal of Control Input Cable (+) 6 at Control Module 6 and ensure it is fully seated in its mating port, closing the previously observed open connection between Control Module 5 and Control Module 6., outcome="Control Input Cable (+) 6 is fully seated at port 'p' of Control Module 6 and is connected together with Control Output Cable (+) 5. Port 'n' of Control Module 6 is disconnected (floating).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module 6 main 12V series path,
description: Using continuity tests, check whether Control Module 6’s internal main path correctly routes the incoming + line at port 'p' to its internal switch and then to the outgoing + line at port 'n' (and similarly for the 0V line). Specifically, test continuity from: (a) Control Output Cable (+)5 to CM6 internal switch input; (b) switch input to switch output (with switch ON); and (c) switch output to the outgoing + terminal that should continue to CM7. Repeat analogous checks on the 0V line. Do not change how the external cables are currently plugged; only probe the internal PCB nodes and terminal pins., outcome='Continuity tests between Control Module 6’s internal nodes and the +/0V cables could not be performed because the multimeter tool is unavailable. As a result, no continuity or routing information for either the + line or the 0V line inside CM6 was obtained.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=190.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control Module 6 cabling topology (ports p and n on both faces),
description: Without changing any internal PCB circuitry, visually trace and record how the two cables on the upstream face of Control Module 6 (coming from Control Module 5) and the two cables on the downstream face (going to Control Module 7) are plugged to ports 'p' and 'n'. Determine for each face which physical cable is the + line and which is the 0V line, and whether the + line entering at port 'p' exits from port 'p' or 'n' on the opposite face. Also confirm whether any of these four terminals is left unconnected or doubled together with another cable., outcome='On the upstream face of Control Module 6, the + line is Control Input Cable (+) 6 at port p (doubled with Control Output Cable (+) 5), while the 0 V line is Control Input Cable (−) 6 present on both ports p and n (with Control Output Cable (−) 5 at p and Control Output Cable (−) 6 at n). On the downstream face, the + line is Control Output Cable (+) 6 present on both ports p and n (with Control Input Cable (+) 7 at n), and the 0 V line is Control Output Cable (−) 6 present on both ports p and n (with Control Input Cable (−) 7 at n). The + line entering at port p (Control Input Cable (+) 6) exits from port n as Control Output Cable (+) 6 (no terminals are left unconnected except upstream port n of the + cable, and several terminals are doubled as noted).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=50.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
